# Splint Geo Processor - Secret
#
# This is the ONLY file you create on a new deployment.
# All other settings are in committed env files:
#   .env.target.local      -- SF_API_URL, poll interval (local dev server)
#   .env.target.production -- SF_API_URL, poll interval (splintfactory.com)
#   .env.platform.mac      -- Rhino/Bambu CLI paths for macOS
#   .env.platform.win      -- Rhino/Bambu CLI paths for Windows
#
# Target file is selected by ENV_MODE=production or auto (Windows => production):
#   Mac/Linux unset -> .env.target.local
#   Windows unset   -> .env.target.production
#   ENV_MODE=production -> .env.target.production
# Platform file is always selected by OS (mac vs win).
# Secrets in .env override all other values.
#
# Get your API key from the factory admin UI at /admin/api-keys
# Use SF_API_KEY_LOCAL / SF_API_KEY_PROD to support both environments on one machine.
# SF_API_KEY is a single-key fallback (e.g. Windows prod machine that only targets production).
SF_API_KEY_LOCAL=your-local-server-api-key
SF_API_KEY_PROD=your-production-api-key
# SF_API_KEY=fallback-if-only-one-environment
